{"pin":"BH10505","subcodes":[{"code":"BH10505","anchor":"","first_line":"O my God! O my God! Unite the hearts of Thy servants and reveal to them Thy great purpose.","word_count":"80","subjects":"@divine grace, bounty, confirmations; spiritual capacity, @prayer for unity, @service to others; to the Cause of God","full_text_parts":["O my God!  O my God!  Unite the hearts of Thy servants, and reveal to them Thy great purpose.  May they follow Thy commandments and abide in Thy law.  Help them, O God, in their endeavor, and grant them strength to serve Thee.  O God!  Leave them not to themselves, but guide their steps by the light of Thy knowledge, and cheer their hearts by Thy love.  Verily, Thou art their Helper and their Lord.\n\n## Note:\n*‘Although no original text has been found for the prayer that begins “O my God!  O my God!  Unite the hearts of Thy servants”, it was included in J. E. Esslemont’s “Baha’u’llah and the New Era”, which was written during the lifetime of ‘Abdu’l-Baha....  The Research Department has indicated that further research is required before a conclusion regarding the authenticity of this prayer can be reached.  In the","meantime, the use of this prayer may continue as before.’”\n\n*(From a letter dated 26 July 2012 written on behalf of the Universal House of Justice to an individual believer)"],"translations":[{"language":"it","lang_name":"Italian"},{"language":"hi","lang_name":"Hindi"},{"language":"dih","lang_name":"Kumiai"},{"language":"hz","lang_name":"Herero"},{"language":"dak","lang_name":"Dakota"},{"language":"kn","lang_name":"Kannada"},{"language":"bs","lang_name":"Bosnian"},{"language":"pl","lang_name":"Polish"},{"language":"sw","lang_name":"Swahili"},{"language":"tpi","lang_name":"Tok Pisin"},{"language":"sr","lang_name":"Serbian"},{"language":"ur","lang_name":"Urdu"},{"language":"fj","lang_name":"Fijian"},{"language":"ro","lang_name":"Romanian"},{"language":"th","lang_name":"Thai"},{"language":"fy","lang_name":"Western Frisian"},{"